38","1150–Male":"1150–Deceased","1152–Female":"1152–Deceased","about 1250":"about 1250","before 1203":"before 1203","1152":"1152","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1238":"1238","1203":"1203","1269":"1269","about 1203":"about 1203","about 1269":"about 1269","Bef 1180":"before 1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England":"Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England","Barnsley, Yorkshire, England":"Barnsley, Yorkshire, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Reppes","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Erik.  German Ingwald, Kurt.","Germanized form of Sorbian <b>Rěpa</b> ‘beet’ (see   Repa  ), and possibly also of some other similar (like-sounding) Slavic cognate."],"variants":[{"name":"Repa","meanings":["Czech (<b>Řepa</b>); Slovak and Slovenian; Hungarian (<b>Répa</b>): from Czech <i>řepa</i> and Slovak <i>repa</i> ‘beet’, Slovenian <i>repa</i> ‘turnip’, and Hungarian <i>répa</i> ‘carrot’ (a loanword from Slavic languages), applied as a nickname or as a metonymic occupational name for a grower or seller of the produce of the field. The Sorbian cognate, <b>Rěpa</b> ‘beet’, is apparently found in Germanized forms, only (see   Reppe   and   Riepe  )."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Anne Reppes was born before 1180, her father, Unknown Reppes, was 30 and her mother, Mrs Reppes, was 27. She married William Woodhouse before 1203, in Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1269."},"et":{"Bef 1180–about 1269":"enne 1180–umbes 1269","1180–1269":"1180–1269","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1203–1238":"1203–1238","1150–Male":"1150–Surnud","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","about 1250":"umbes 1250","before 1203":"enne 1203","1152":"1152","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1238":"1238","1203":"1203","1269":"1269","about 1203":"umbes 1203","about 1269":"umbes 1269","Bef 1180":"enne 1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England":"Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England","Barnsley, Yorkshire, England":"Barnsley, Yorkshire, England"},"fi":{"Bef 1180–about 1269":"ennen vuotta 1180–noin 1269","1180–1269":"1180–1269","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1203–1238":"1203–1238","1150–Male":"1150–Kuollut","1152–Female":"1152–Kuollut","about 1250":"noin 1250","before 1203":"ennen vuotta 1203","1152":"1152","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1238":"1238","1203":"1203","1269":"1269","about 1203":"noin 1203","about 1269":"noin 1269","Bef 1180":"ennen vuotta 1180","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England":"Wentworth Woodhouse, Yorkshire, England","Barnsley, Yorkshire, England":"Barnsley, Yorkshire, England"},"fr":{"Bef 1180–about 1269":"avant 1180–environ 1269","1180–1269":"1180–1269","1171–1250":"1171–1250","1203–1238":"1203–1238","1150–Male":"1150–Décédé","1152–Female":"1152–Décédée","about 1250":"environ 1250","before 1203":"avant 1203","1152":"1152","1250":"1250","1150":"1150","1171":"1171","1180":"1180","1238":"1238","1203":"1203","1269":"1269","about 1203":"environ 1203","about 1269":"environ 1269","Bef 1180":"avant 1180","Yorkshi